On learning this Caesar advanced to Ariminum, thereby leaving his province and practically declaring war against the senate. He rapidly took possession of a large number of towns in Italy, and so great was the alarm at Rome that the consuls fied to Capua. Domitius made a brief stand at Corfinium, but the town soon yielded to Caesar. Thereupon Pompey went to Brundisium, whither he was followed by Caesar, who began to block up the harbour.
